pageContext.claim: “The attorney general [Keith Ellison]-- Well, I will say one thing about him. He was the first one, I think, or just about, him and one other person, on day one he said, 'You know that Trump,' this is four years ago, 'You know that Trump is going to win, don't you?' They said, 'What do you mean?' He said, 'Trump is going to win." So in one way can't be so stupid, right?”
pageContext.analysis: Ellison did not say that Trump was "going to win"; he said Trump "might" win the Republican nomination: His comment earned a round of chuckles from the other guests, who at the time thought it was ridiculous, but he did not make such a declarative comment.
